Netflix Premium is by far the most popular Netflix package among South Africans. This was one of the findings of the Netflix 2020 Survey conducted by MyBroadband. The survey was completed by 1,867 tech-savvy South Africans and provides an excellent overview of the local market. Of those who took part in the survey, 80% said they subscribe to Netflix. Of these users, 53% said they have a Netflix Premium subscription. 35% of the Netflix users said they have a Standard package, while 12% are signed up to the Basic package. Netflix’s three packages all give users access to the streaming service’s full content library. Where they differ, however, is in terms of the maximum resolution you can stream content in and the number of devices you can watch Netflix on at the same time. The graph below details the most popular Netflix packages in South Africa. Click on the graph below to enlarge it. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-341693 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Netflix-Packages-640x360.png" alt="Netflix Packages" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Netflix-Packages-640x360.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Netflix-Packages-600x337.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Netflix-Packages-768x431.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Netflix-Packages.png 1157w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Survey respondents who do not have Netflix were also asked about why they do not subscribe to the streaming service. The most popular reasons for people not having Netflix are listed below. Of these respondents who do not have Netflix, however, 51% said they planned to sign up to Netflix in 2020.